com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.config

Class XmlPropsConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.config.XmlPropsConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropsConfig

    @ThreadSafe
public final class XmlPropsConfig
extends Object
implements PropsConfig
    Represents configuration that is specified via XML document. This implementation uses XMLConfiguration in order to read cachedProps from XML. See Apache Commons Configuration for details; e.g. Variable Interpolation (aka Property Substitution) is a very useful functionality. However note also that Apache Commons Configuration seem to violate its specification sometimes, e.g. you can't preserve spaces by using xml:space="preserve" as specified in XMLConfiguration.

    Semicolon ';' (Unicode code point U+003B) is used as delimiter in multiple properties (see AbstractConfiguration.setListDelimiter(char)). One can escape the semicolon character in the multiple value by using backslash '\' (Unicode code point U+005C).
